<section class="page-header">
<h2>Get in Touch</h2>
<p>Questions, research requests, and volunteer inquiries are encouraged.</p>
</section>

<section class="cards">
<div class="card">
<h3>Location</h3>
<p>Salvage Fisherman's Museum<br>52 Mountainview Rd<br>Salvage, NL, A0G 0J2</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Research and Genealogy</h3>
<p>Ask staff or volunteers about church records, family history resources, photographs, and local history files available at the museum.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Donations and Loans</h3>
<p>Please contact the museum before bringing artifacts, documents, or photographs for review by the collections committee. Note that we have limited capacity for new acquisitions at this time.&nbsp;</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="content">
<h2>Before You Visit</h2>
<p>The museum is open seasonally and admission is by donation. Visitors are encouraged to sign the guest book, ask questions, browse the gift shop, and continue their journey in Salvage through the numerous hiking trails on the Damnable Trail system.&nbsp;</p>

<div class="note">
<h3>Contact Details</h3>
<p>Email <a href="mailto:salvagefishermansmuseum@gmail.com">salvagefishermansmuseum@gmail.com</a> for museum questions, research requests, potential donations, loans, or volunteer inquiries.</p>
</div>
</section>

<footer>
